30/10/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- Greece will host a secure and successful Summer Olympics, US State Department spokesman Richard Boucher reiterated on Wednesday (29 October).
He added that Greece is working with several countries, including the United States, to ensure the full safety of the Olympic Games.
His remarks were in response to a recent article in <I>To Vima</I> newspaper, which claims a report by US experts found security problems.
In other news Wednesday, Prime Minister Costas Simitis and Development Minister Akis Tsohatzopoulos announced that the National Tourism Organisation would create a new subsidiary to handle all tourism marketing issues related to the Olympics.
Overall, Simitis wants to increase by 2 per cent the share of the tourist sector in the economy.
(ANA, MPA, AFP - 29/10/03)
